# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# V5.0 — Odds Collection Crontab
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Install with:  crontab -e  (then paste relevant lines)
#
# All times are in the server's local timezone.
# Adjust if server is not EST — the times below assume EST.
#
# Env vars required in cron:
#   ODDSAPI_KEY=your_key_here
#   SGO_API_KEY=your_key_here  (optional, future provider)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

SHELL=/bin/bash
PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin
PROJECT=/home/derek/Documents/stock/v5.0
ODDSAPI_KEY=your_oddsapi_key_here
# SGO_API_KEY=your_sgo_key_here

# ── Opening Odds (12:05 AM EST daily) ───────────────────
# Captures the day's opening lines as early as possible
5 0 * * *  cd $PROJECT && python3 scripts/odds_scheduler.py --mode opening --once --normalize >> logs/cron_opening.log 2>&1

# ── Current Odds Snapshots (every hour, 6 AM – 11 PM EST) ─
# Hourly snapshots to track line movement throughout the day
# Runs once per hour; increase frequency by adding more entries
# or running in loop mode via systemd (see below)
0 6-23 * * *  cd $PROJECT && python3 scripts/odds_scheduler.py --mode current --once >> logs/cron_current.log 2>&1

# ── Injuries Imports (every hour, all providers with support) ─
# Runs injuries-only importer so injury state is refreshed independently
# of the daily pipeline.
0 * * * *  cd $PROJECT/importers && npm run import:injuries:hourly >> ../logs/cron_injuries.log 2>&1

# ── Closing Odds (every minute, peak game hours) ────────
# Polls for games starting soon and grabs final lines
# MLB/NBA/NHL typically 7-10 PM EST; NFL Sunday 1 PM & 4 PM
# Run every minute during peak hours to catch 5-min pre-game window
* 12-23 * * *  cd $PROJECT && python3 scripts/odds_scheduler.py --mode closing --once >> logs/cron_closing.log 2>&1

# ── Full Daily Pipeline (6 AM EST) ──────────────────────
# Main pipeline: import all data, normalize, train, predict
0 6 * * *  cd $PROJECT && python3 scripts/daily_pipeline.py >> logs/cron_pipeline.log 2>&1

# ── Model Drift Detection (7 AM EST, after pipeline) ────
# Checks rolling 7-day accuracy vs 30-day baseline; exits 1 if drift detected
0 7 * * *  cd $PROJECT && /home/derek/Documents/stock/.venv/bin/python3 scripts/model_drift_detector.py >> logs/cron_drift.log 2>&1

# ── Recurring Curated + DuckDB Refresh (every 30 min) ───
# Auto-detects changed normalized files and refreshes curated outputs + DuckDB once per run.
*/30 * * * *  cd $PROJECT && /home/derek/Documents/stock/.venv/bin/python3 scripts/recurring_curated_refresh.py --mode auto >> logs/cron_curated_refresh.log 2>&1

# ── Full Curated Rebuild (daily 6:25 AM EST) ─────────────
# Rebuild all category/sport parquets and bulk refresh DuckDB catalog.
25 6 * * *  cd $PROJECT && /home/derek/Documents/stock/.venv/bin/python3 scripts/recurring_curated_refresh.py --mode full >> logs/cron_curated_refresh_full.log 2>&1

# ── Season Simulator (Tuesday 8 AM EST) ─────────────────
# Monte Carlo projections: championships, awards, brackets, draft lottery
0 8 * * 2  cd $PROJECT && python3 scripts/season_simulator.py --sport all --simulations 10000 >> logs/cron_simulator.log 2>&1

# ── Live Model (continuous during game hours) ────────────
# Adjusts win probabilities during live games (polls every 60s)
# Run during typical game hours: 12 PM - 1 AM EST
0 12 * * *  cd $PROJECT && timeout 13h python3 scripts/live_model.py --daemon --interval 60 >> logs/cron_live.log 2>&1

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ALTERNATIVE: systemd service for continuous collection
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Instead of cron, run odds_scheduler.py as a long-running service:
#
#   python3 scripts/odds_scheduler.py --mode all --interval 60
#
# This will:
#   1. Collect opening odds immediately
#   2. Collect closing odds for any imminent games
#   3. Snapshot current odds every 60 minutes
#   4. Loop continuously (current + closing)
#
# systemd unit file example (/etc/systemd/system/odds-collector.service):
#
#   [Unit]
#   Description=V5.0 Odds Collector
#   After=network.target
#
#   [Service]
#   Type=simple
#   User=derek
#   WorkingDirectory=/home/derek/Documents/stock/v5.0
#   Environment=ODDSAPI_KEY=your_key_here
#   ExecStart=/usr/bin/python3 scripts/odds_scheduler.py --mode all --interval 60
#   Restart=on-failure
#   RestartSec=60
#
#   [Install]
#   WantedBy=multi-user.target
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# INTERVAL TUNING (for credit limit increases)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Default: --interval 60 (1 hour between snapshots)
#
# If your OddsAPI credit limit increases, reduce the interval:
#   --interval 30   → every 30 min (2x credits)
#   --interval 15   → every 15 min (4x credits)
#   --interval 5    → every 5 min  (12x credits, good for live tracking)
#
# Credit budget estimate (per sport, per day):
#   60 min interval: ~18 requests/day   (6 AM – 11 PM)
#   30 min interval: ~36 requests/day
#   15 min interval: ~72 requests/day
#    5 min interval: ~216 requests/day
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
